description.plain: Carrie Marie Underwood (born March 10, 1983) is an American country music singer, songwriter, and actress. She rose to fame as the winner of the fourth season of American Idol in 2005. Underwood has since become a multi-platinum selling recording artist, a winner of six Grammy Awards, sixteen Billboard Music Awards, seven American Music Awards and ten Academy of Country Music Awards, among several others. As a songwriter, she has been nominated for a Golden Globe Award for Best Original Song. Underwood is also a two-time winner of the Academy of Country Music Entertainer of the Year award and the first woman to win such an award twice (2009/10). Underwood was inducted into and became a member of the Grand Ole Opry in 2008. She was also inducted into the Oklahoma Music Hall of Fame in 2009.

songs.full_title: Cry Pretty by Carrie Underwood
songs.title: Cry Pretty

description.plain:
This song follows Underwood’s journey of coming to terms with herself and her difference of appearance after an accident. She fell on the steps of her home and had to receive 40-50 stitches on her face.

In “Cry Pretty”, she exposes her vulnerability and insecurities and gives power to them, empowering and enabling others to feel comfortable doing the same. She tells listeners to join her in embracing their emotions even when they aren’t “pretty”. It is common for people in this society both men and women, to suppress their emotions because they feel they will be viewed as weak or ugly if seen crying or under turmoil. She sends a message to those fans about how unrealistic it is for them to expect to be able to maintain an attractive appearance when going through distress and to embrace how they look. This song promotes healthy expectations, body love, anti-shame and general acceptance.

songs.title: The Champion

description.plain:
On the 6th of January 2018, “Champion” was officially previewed during the NFL Wild Card game between the Atlanta Falcons and Los Angeles Rams.

Carrie Underwood’s Instagram page also posted a clip previewing the song:



The first collaboration between 7-times Grammy Winner/Country superstar Carrie Underwood and rapper Ludacris leaked two days before its official release which was set for Friday January 12th.

Underwood has not released a solo single since she dropped “Dirty Laundry” from her 2015 album Storyteller back in September 2016. Her most recent collaboration was “The Fighter”  duet released in February 2017 and featured on Keith Urban’s Grammy-nominated Ripcord album.

The song will also be the first new music Carrie releases since revealing facial injuries caused after falling outside her Nashville home back in November 2017. She also revealed that the accident was much more serious than originally thought, resulting in “between 40 and 50 stitches” to her face.

songs.title: Smoke Break

description.plain:
“Smoke Break” is the lead single from Carrie Underwood’s fifth studio album, Storyteller. The track, written with Hillary Lindsey and Chris DeStefano, premiered on August 20, 2015 at country radio and was digitally released on August 21.

Underwood announced “Smoke Break” and accompanying album Storyteller in a video posted to Facebook, in which she also described its meaning:

The song itself is … one of those story songs that I feel like everyone can relate to about how life is so hectic and it’s so nice if and when you actually get to kind of step away for a second. We all need that time to ourselves, to get to take a break.

According to USA Today, the track came to life while getting stuck working one of the other tracks on Storyteller:

We were writing and kept taking breaks to go outside because we were getting a little stuck on a song we were already working on. It was so beautiful outside, that we had a hard time focusing so we decided to write a song about taking breaks! “Smoke Break” seemed like a great title, so we ran with it!

“Two Black Cadillacs” is the third single taken from Carrie Underwood’s fourth studio album Blown Away.

“Two Black Cadillacs” tells the story of two women who, when they realize they are both dating the same guy, set aside their differences and decide to take care of things together.

The six minute long music video for the track, was directed by veteran video-maker Paul R. Brown, also received nomination for Video of the Year at the Academy of Country Music Awards.

description.plain: “Just a Dream” is a song in which the listener is never quite sure about whether it’s reality or a dream. The song describes a young woman heading to the church to wed her fiance, but quickly spirals into a funeral. Whether the insistence that “this is just a dream” is literal or just wishful thinking is left up to the listener to decide.

“Good Girl” is a song by American country music recording artist Carrie Underwood. The song was released as the lead single from Underwood’s fourth studio album, Blown Away.

Lyrically, the narrator is offering advice to a girl who’s a little too naive for her own good. The narrator is a little more worldly than the girl she’s talking to, and she realizes that the guy this girl’s interested in isn’t all that he says he is.

songs.full_title: Nobody Ever Told You by Carrie Underwood
songs.title: Nobody Ever Told You

description.plain:
“Nobody Ever Told You” is a self-empowerment anthem for young girls who are struggling with their insecurities. Growing up in the modern world, there is so much pressure on young people, and society in general, to look and act a certain way, especially now with the added impact of social media.

In “Nobody Ever Told You”, Carrie is saying that it doesn’t matter what you look like, if someone else is prettier than you, or how you dress, as long as you are true to yourself. What you don’t like about yourself, some one else may find attractive.
